DE_KEYSTONE_BETA - a Bomb/Defuse map for Counter-Strike Source

Made for Gamebanana's "The Kepler-22b" Mapping Contest

Author - LexxoR

Building time - ~21 day

My entry for the Kepler-22b Mapping Contest.

Terorists have boarded the Keystone IV spacecraft. The ship's personal guards have been called to fend off the boarders. Intelligence suggests the terrorists may be in possession of an explosive device. Caution is advised, especially around windows.

Features:
- Dynamic layout, making for claustrophobic and fast-paced bomb defusal gameplay
- Airlocks!
- Custom skybox depicting Kepler-22b
- Radar Overview

Playtesters with different computer specs did not report framerate or crashing issues.

Author's Note:

After about 30 hours work over a hellish month, 6 hours of 4v4 playtesting, final exams, large coffees, and about four listens of Rise Against's entire 2010 Rock Am Ring concert, here it is.

I hope you have as much fun playing this map as I did making it

Story line
On December 5, 2011 Astronomers discovered Kepler-22b, the first planet known to orbit a single star Within ITS habitable zone. In 2061, after 50 years studying and preparing to colonize the planet, the conglomerate of Earth Space Agencies was ready to launch the "Keystone IV," the largest, most expensive and most complex machine ever conceived - to travel to and colonize Kepler-22b.
On November 2, two years after the initial launch. The Keystone IV finally reached it's destination Kepler-22b. Unfortunatly for the ESA's crew, they weren't welcome there. An alien spaceship chopped half of the Keystone IV. The shield they used during the hyperspace travel has been destroyed in only one shot. That could have been the end. But then, coming out from nowhere, the main ship Scarlet-I launched in secret by the DTT Corporation hitted the alien spaceship with it's shield, cutting the ennemy ship in half and saving the Keystone IV. The alien managed to mind control half of the crew during the battle, they're now trying to C4 the whole spaceship. The civil part of the crew has been evacuated to Scarlet-I, the military now need to recover the control of the ship. Keystone being half destroyed, there's a lot of spacequake.
About the development
After 3 weeks of hard work and more than 200 hours of SDK I finally managed to make it before the deadline. Close, that's true, but in time. Anyway, I barely slept this month and I'll be sure to rest this week :3 Of course I could have done better but in limited time I think I've did my best.
Some values
KeySIV that's :
Over 100 brand new textures and 91 materials
50 new models
1300 point entities
200 bloc entities
230mo for the light version, uncompressed (81mo compressed)
More than 3Go with the HD version that sit on my computer. (Too heavy to be uploaded, however I plan something for it)
Video by EXpMiNi
Announcement
Also I announce that all theses custom resources will be released in a resource pack for the community within the next two weeks. I hope you guys will enjoy this news. As always, please report bugs if you encounter them.

de_karachi_b1 - Bomb-Defuse

Welcome to the deadly streets of Karachi, Pakistan. 
Intelligence reports have been mounting recently saying that
A terrorist strike is imminent. There appears to be an 
arms cache in the west of the city. This looks to be their main target.
We cannot allow them to gain control of these arms. 
The terrorist faction's MO in the past has been
to create a diversion elsewhere in the city, often hitting public targets. 

CTs must focus on the arms cache, but are obligated to protect the locals
if possible. We have a CT unit on standby a few blocks from the arms cache. 
Once the word is given they will proceed with Operation-Dustkiller.

Terrorists: plant the bomb by the porch or at the bus.

Counter Terrorists: defuse the bomb and/or neutralize the terrorists

The crazies have broken out of their "terrorist cells" at the courthouse, and they're planning to bomb the place to facilitate their escape. The SWAT team, of course, has just arrived to stop them.

The terrorists can either plant the bomb at the base of the statue above the courtroom or inside the main security control room just below the prison. The statue is closer, but it's a very open area, with enemies coming from all directions. The control room is harder to get to, but it's more easily defended once the bomb is planted.

There are 40 spawn points. There are multiple ways to get to either bomb site, including from the outside courtyard and from the basement (to bomb site B). Sniper points are everywhere, so watch your head.

There is an alternate way for the terrorists to get to bomb site B. After existing the prison spawn point, the terrorists can turn right into the third-floor balcony area instead of running down the corridor to bomb site A.

In the balcony, use the crates to jump onto the fence. You can then jump onto a lamp fixture extending out from the side of the building. From the light fixture, you can then jump onto the perimeter wall, and then jump down to ground level without suffering damage.

This route is trickier, but also sneakier. The basement also provides a detour to the bomb site. You can surprise the CT by showing up at bomb site B largely undetected.

Bomb/Defuse map based on the famous Combat Arms' map (Junk Flea).

Map: An important junkyard placed in the south of
California. The place reduce junk and recicle them
to use it in shotguns shells. This place is the only
provider of this recicled plastic to make shells. If
the recicle cycle stops by any reason, shotguns will
need to be removed from the US Army.


Terrorists: destroy the electrical center in order
to make the factory stop working and prevent
terrorists from all over the world being killed by
the US shotguns.


Counter Terrorists: prevent Terrorists get inside the
electrical system.


Tip: the electrical center is next to the Counter
Terrorists Spawn with two red lights.



Instalation: extract and replace the maps folder in your cstrike directory.

Official website (map downloads/updates) : www.poutre.free.fr

The zip archive must be unzipped into the directory Steam/Steamapps/youraccount/counter-strike source/cstrike respecting the folder hierarchy.

All models, materials, sounds, nav mesh and additional elements are embedded into the bsp.

The files navplace.db, cstrike_english.txt and cstrike_french.txt are optional and the map can work without them. However, they allow more appropriate place names to be displayed under the radar and in the chat. Be warned that as long as these files are installed, they prevent the game to have access to the files bearing the same names in the gcf (cache) and to the potential modifications that Valve can make to them. If you're unsure, unzip only the .bsp
